headline: Why Dollar General Stock Zoomed Nearly 17% Higher This Week
summary: The company got a real lift from its impressive first-quarter earnings report.  In retrospect that wasn't surprising, as the company simply crushed it in its latest earnings report, and analysts fell over themselves publishing bullish new takes on its stock.  Dollar General delivered its first-quarter figures Tuesday morning, and investors couldn't wait to pile into its shares.

headline: The Score: Tesla, Cleveland-Cliffs, Dollar General and More Stocks That Defined the Week
summary: President Trump unveiled the higher duties at a rally on May 30 promoting a $14 billion deal between Japan’s  Nippon Steel  and  U.S. Steel  which he said would ensure U.S. control over the company.  Trump said that the move to increase the levies, which took effect June 4, would bolster the domestic industry and protect U.S. jobs.  Cleveland-Cliffs  shares surged 23% on Monday, while  Steel Dynamics  and  Nucor  shares each gained 10%.

headline: Dollar General Stock Is Rallying. Is It Still a Bargain?
summary: The reasons for that volatility may partially explain why shares of Dollar General are up more than 50%.  Shares of Dollar General (NYSE: DG) have had a great run so far in 2025 and are outperforming the S&P 500 by a wide margin.  Is Dollar General stock still cheap, or has this year's rally made it too expensive?
